    IAdaptation<org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Dependency,java.util.List<org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Dependency>>, ITransformation<org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Dependency,java.util.List<org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Dependency>>

    public class DependencyWithAbstractMembersAdaptation
extends AbstractRelationshipWithAbstractMembersAdaptation<org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Dependency>
    a DependencyWithAbstractMembersAdaptation concrete class that is used to adapt a UML dependency having abstract members by moving down the dependency into each non abstract child of each of its abstract members.

    The adaptation consists of creating a list of target dependencies having the same owning package as the source dependency to adapt, such that the members of each target dependency consist of the original non abstract members of the source dependency and a non abstract child of the original abstract member of the source dependency.
    Author:
    Bachar Rima

      • DependencyWithAbstractMembersAdaptation

        public DependencyWithAbstractMembersAdaptation(org.eclipse.uml2.uml.Dependency source)
                                        throws NotATypeException,
                                               NotADependencyWithAnAbstractMemberException
        Creates a dependency with abstract members adaptation having source as its source dependency to adapt, then applies the adaptation to obtain the list of target dependencies with no abstract members, such that the members of each target dependency consist of the original non abstract members of the source dependency and a non abstract child of the original abstract member of the source dependency. It then cleans the post-adaptation residues.
        Parameters:
        source - the source dependency to adapt
        Throws:
        NotATypeException - if the provided source dependency has a client or a supplier that is not a typed element
        NotADependencyWithAnAbstractMemberException - if the provided source dependency doesn't have abstract members
